      第 2 筆 ---------------------------------------------------------------------




系統識別號
U0026-0812200911384629


論文名稱(中文) 
      
安平歷史聚落建築景觀風格維護之研究


論文名稱(英文) 
      
A Study of Conservation and Townscape in An-Ping Settlement


校院名稱
成功大學


系所名稱(中)
建築學系碩博士班


系所名稱(英)
Department of Architecture


學年度
93


學期
2


出版年
94


研究生(中文)
陳彥儒


學號
n7692117


學位類別
碩士


語文別
中文


口試日期
2005-07-22


論文頁數
135頁


口試委員
召集委員-陳逸傑
口試委員-盧圓華
指導教授-孫全文



關鍵字(中)
保存式的都市更新都市景觀安平歷史風貌維護


關鍵字(英)
TownscapeHistorical PreservationPreservative Urban RenewalAn-Ping


學科別分類



中文摘要
　　在急遽改變的社會結構以及經濟發展的影響下，台灣的許多歷史城鎮與聚落已經遭到無情的破壞，許多珍貴的建築遺產及聚居場所逐漸被突兀的現代建築所取代。而承載台灣三百多年歷史的安平聚落一樣難以逃過現代都市發展與現代建築樣式的破壞，今日的安平聚落所呈現出建築景觀風貌是新舊建築混雜、景觀風貌上衝突混亂與傳統人性空間尺度逐漸消失的安平聚落。在這樣狀況下，安平歷史聚落逐漸的與台灣其他城鎮同質化，而喪失其歷史聚落應有之歷史風貌與景觀特色。在面對如此複雜的聚落建築景觀風格的狀況下，本研究之主要研究內容如下： 1. 透過對安平聚落歷史發展的研究，進而歸納出聚落在景觀風貌上的轉變，並分析傳統民居的形式構成，加以整理出其形式特色與特徵，以作為訂定都市設計規範時之依據與參考。 2. 本研究藉由重點性的基礎調查，調查的內容包含了聚落空間體系、土地區劃模式與建築物樓層高度等各項現況，並配和聚落中具連續意象的街巷空間與廣場的動靜態的視覺景觀分析，歸納出當前聚落建築景觀風格的潛力與乾擾因子。 3. 在劃定分區方面，本研究採用疊合相關歷史資源的方式，將歷史聚落劃分為核心保存區、歷史發展區與外圍緩衝區等面狀管制分區，以及歷史街巷沿街面管制與週邊道路沿街面管制兩種線狀管制區分。 4. 在維護機制上方面，本文提出以「保存式都市更新」作為機制。保存式都市更新依照不同區位與不同現況的建築物，分別對其提出維護、整建、重建與拆除四種的更新改善方式。


英文摘要
　With the rapid transform of social structure and economic development, a lot of historical sites and towns of Taiwan have already suffered from merciless destruction. Most ancient buildings and community places have been gradually replaced by towering modern building. The An-Ping settlement with more than three hundred years Taiwanese history also could not escape from the destruction of modern urban development and builds. Nowadays, the landscapes of An-Ping buildings combine with both new and old buildings, conflicts between chaos landscapes, and the losses of traditional humanity spaces. With this situation, An-Ping is increasing similar to other towns in Taiwan. The unique strength of An-Ping in his historical landscape has gradually lost. With the challenge of complicated townscape, the main objectives of this research are addressed as follows: 1.	Generalizing the settlement transition of landscape from the historical development of An-Ping settlement. In accordance with the traditional life style of residences, the characteristics and features are analyzed and induced, as a reference for the standard of urban designs. 2.	With several focal basic investigations, including settlement spaces, land divisions, the height of buildings, etc., and allay spaces with successive prospects and square with different visional landscape, the potential and interferon of current landscape are analyzed and included.3.	In terms of land divisions, with a stack of historical resources, the historical settlements have been divided into two restrained parts, that is, net and line restrained areas. Net restrained parts include core preservation, historical development and outer buffer zone. Line restrained parts include historical streets and periphery roads.4.	From the aspect of maintaining mechanism, the “Preservative Urban Renewal” is purposed by this research. The preservative urban renewal, according to the buildings with different areas and situations, recommend four improving program, that is, preservation, repair, rebuilding, and dismantling.


